about_me.des: I am an Aeroespace Engineering with experience developing software Space Surveillance and Tracking applications.

projects.jalpc: This project is my project. I use javescript to get repo's information all my repos have only one request.
projects.cpython: This project is other's project. I use another request to get repo's information.

career.SatCen_des: I am part of the Operations Team of the EU SST Front Desk at the European Union Satellite Center.
career.Phd_Airbus_name: PhD researcher at Airbus Defence and Space
career.Phd_Airbus_des: Worked in the field of Space Surveillance and Tracking, developing a software tool that performed the full cataloguing chain of space debris, from initial sensor scheduling, data acquisition, processing and correlation up until orbit determination and propagation. My research was focused on developing new correlation algorithms for cataloguing space debris using optical systems.
career.Thesis_Airbus_name: MSc Final year thesis at Airbus Defence and Space
career.Thesis_Airbus_des: I did my MSc thesis in Airbus Defence and Space developoing an Orbit Determination tool for space debris.
career.MSc_cranfield_name: MSc in Astronautics and Space Engineering at Cranfield University
career.MSc_cranfield_desc: In September 2016 I graduated from a Master in Astronautics and Space Engineering at Cranfield University, where I was enrolled as part of a double degree with the Technical University of Madrid (UPM). I received the Airbus Defence and Space Prize for excellent perfomance during the MSc.
career.MSc_upm_name: MSc in Aeronautical Engineering at Technical University of Madrid (UPM)
career.MSc_upm_desc: In Septembber 2016 I graduated from the MSc in Aeronautical Engineering, gaining professional habilitation to practise the regulated profession of Aeroespace Engineer required by Spanish law. I did an specialization in Space Vehicles.
career.everis_name: Internship in Everis Aerospace, Defence and Security
career.everis_des: During my internship in Everis Aerospace and defence I was in charge of developing a tool to simulate the dynamics of low range missile, focusing on the theoretical modelling of the aerodynamic forces.
career.BSc_upm_name: BSc in Aeroespace Engineering at Technical University of Madrid (UPM)
career.BSc_upm_desc: In July 2014 I graduted from a Bachelor in Aeroespace Engineering with an intesification in Aerospace Sciences and Technologies. I was granted with a research scholarship by the Spanish cience and Education Ministry to develop my final year thesis.
